                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Tech duo on a hiring spree in Calcutta
          A STAFF REPORTER                          (From left) Bengal IT minister Debesh Das, CII (eastern region) chairman Sandipan Chakravortty and former Nasscom president Kiran Karnik in Calcutta on Wednesday. A Telegraph picture                                  
	Calcutta, Aug. 6: Capgemini and HCL Infosystems are looking to scale up their presence in the city.        
	While Capgemini is set to ramp up its headcount to 2,000 by the end of 2009, HCL Infosystems can recruit anywhere between 1,000 and 1,500 in the next 12 months.        
	We will be shifting to our new campus in the Unitech SEZ by the end of next week. We have taken up 200,000 sq ft of office space, which can accommodate 1,700 people. We currently have 835 employees in our 80,000-square-foot office in Sector V, said Baru S. Rao, CEO of Capgemini, on the sidelines of the CII-ICT East 2008 seminar here today.        
	Capgemini, which has 19,800 employees, plans to increase its headcount to 23,000 by the end of December. It is also looking at acquisitions in the business process outsourcing space in areas such as engineering services.         
	HCL Infosystems Ltd, part of the $4-billion HCL group, has got land for a Calcutta campus. The city office will become a consulting hub for the IT major in system integration and employ around 1,000 to 1,500 people in next 12 months.        
	HCL will be hiring around 1,000 to 1,500 people in the course of the next 12 months. The company now employs over 500 people in the city but mostly for its PC business, said state IT minister Debesh Das.                                                                                                                                                               
